n Bani's cousin, Maya is found dead in the first class compartment.","genre_ids":[80,18,9648,53],"popularity":0.1253,"vote_count":2,"poster_path":"/tWcmpAfDVC0YpMGOHKcP3ot2DL0.jpg","release_date":"1958-01-01","vote_average":7,"backdrop_path":null,"original_title":"12 O'Clock","original_language":"hi"},{"id":120,"adult":false,"title":"The Lord of the Rings: The Fellowship of the Ring","video":false,"overview":"Young hobbit Frodo Baggins, after inheriting a mysterious ring from his uncle Bilbo, must leave his home in order to keep it from falling into the hands of its evil creator. Along the way, a fellowship is formed to protect the ringbearer and make sure that the ring arrives at its final destination: Mt. Doom, the only place where it can be destroyed.","genre_ids":[12,14,28],"popularity":26.6058,"vote_count":27061,"poster_path":"/6oom5QYQ2yQTMJIbnvbkBL9cHo6.jpg","release_date":"2001-12-18","vote_average":8.429,"backdrop_path":"/z51Wzj94hvAIsWfknifKTqKJRwp.jpg","original_title":"The Lord of the Rings: The Fellowship of the Ring","original_language":"en"},{"id":121,"adult":false,"title":"The Lord of the Rings: The Two Towers","video":false,"overview":"Frodo Baggins and the other members of the Fellowship continue on their sacred quest to destroy the One Ring--but on separate paths. Their destinies lie at two towers--Orthanc Tower in Isengard, where the corrupt wizard Saruman awaits, and Sauron's fortress at Barad-dur, deep within the dark lands of Mordor. Frodo and Sam are trekking to Mordor to destroy the One Ring of Power while Gimli, Legolas and Aragorn search for the orc-captured Merry and Pippin. All along, nefarious wizard Saruman awaits the Fellowship members at the Orthanc Tower in Isengard.","genre_ids":[12,14,28],"popularity":17.7989,"vote_count":23478,"poster_path":"/5VTN0pR8gcqV3EPUHHfMGnJYN9L.jpg","release_date":"2002-12-18","vote_average":8.413,"backdrop_path":"/kWYfW2Re0rUDE6IHhy4CRuKWeFr.jpg","original_title":"The Lord of the Rings: The Two Towers","original_language":"en"},{"id":122,"adult":false,"title":"The Lord of the Rings: The Return of the King","video":false,"overview":"As armies mass for a final battle that will decide the fate of the world--and powerful, ancient forces of Light and Dark compete to determine the outcome--one member of the Fellowship of the Ring is revealed as the noble heir to the throne of the Kings of Men. Yet, the sole hope for triumph over evil lies with a brave hobbit, Frodo, who, accompanied by his loyal friend Sam and the hideous, wretched Gollum, ventures deep into the very dark heart of Mordor on his seemingly impossible quest to destroy the Ring of Power.​","genre_ids":[12,14,28],"popularity":23.6525,"vote_count":26078,"poster_path":"/rCzpDGLbOoPwLjy3OAm5NUPOTrC.jpg","release_date":"2003-12-17","vote_average":8.494,"backdrop_path":"/2u7zbn8EudG6kLlBzUYqP8RyFU4.jpg","original_title":"The Lord of the Rings: The Return of the King","original_language":"en"},{"id":123,"adult":false,"title":"The Lord of the Rings","video":false,"overview":"Young Hobbit Frodo Baggins is thrown into an amazing adventure when he's tasked with destroying the One Ring, created by the dark lord Sauron. Frodo must travel in a small fellowship of nine warriors and accomplices. But it won't be an easy journey for the Fellowship of the Ring, on the ultimate quest to rid Middle-earth of evil.","genre_ids":[12,16,14],"popularity":2.9408,"vote_count":1023,"poster_path":"/liW0mjvTyLs7UCumaHhx3PpU4VT.jpg","release_date":"1978-11-15","vote_average":6.6,"backdrop_path":"/TXSxV23MWYkezZ3219gtgcSX6n.jpg","original_title":"The Lord of the Rings","original_language":"en"},{"id":462964,"adult":false,"title":"Daava","video":false,"overview":"Arjun is police officer and he has two stepbrothers, Bhishma and Suraj. Dhaman takes full advantage of this situation, and watches as the brothers go against each other.","genre_ids":[28,18,10749],"popularity":0.3323,"vote_count":2,"poster_path":"/eNfAmY0c1daaq2vlppzTl1mRaOC.jpg","